# Azure Document Intelligence connection.
# Leave these blank (or delete the file) to run with the offline mock extractor.
# Copy to ".env" and fill in to use the real Azure provider — no code changes needed.
#
# The double underscore maps to the "DocumentIntelligence" configuration section.
#
# The endpoint alone is enough: with no ApiKey the extractor authenticates with Entra ID via
# DefaultAzureCredential — locally that means your own `az login` identity, which needs the
# "Cognitive Services User" role on the resource. That's how the deployed app runs too (as its
# managed identity), so there is no key to store anywhere. Set ApiKey only if you'd rather use
# an account key, and note that infra/main.bicep provisions the resource with keys disabled.

DocumentIntelligence__Endpoint=
DocumentIntelligence__ApiKey=
